com.intel.fightclub.dialog.events

Class RetryableDialogEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.fightclub.dialog.events.DialogEvent
      • com.intel.fightclub.dialog.events.RetryableDialogEvent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AllRelevantSensorsConnectedEvent, AppMessageEvent, AudioChannelEvent, BatteryLevelEvent, CoachingCommentaryEvent, DeviceErrorEvent, RelevantSensorsDisconnectedEvent, SensorStatusEvent, VerbosityUpdatedEvent, WearableStatusEvent

    @NotThreadSafe
public abstract class RetryableDialogEvent
extends DialogEvent
    Defines a retryable DialogEvent for which retry attempts will be made if the message cannot be successfully delivered to the DialogManager. Default behavior of a RetryableDialogEvent will be to allow for a maximum of 5 retries, every 500ms.
